remarks.format:
## Remarks

`HBColor` is a value type that wraps the HarfBuzz `hb_color_t` color, which uses BGRA byte ordering packed as `0xBBGGRRAA` (blue in the high byte, alpha in the low byte). This differs from `SKColor`, which uses ARGB (`0xAARRGGBB`).

Use the named properties (`Red`, `Green`, `Blue`, `Alpha`) to access color channels rather than shifting the raw `Value` directly. When retrieving palette colors from a `Face`, the returned `HBColor` values use this BGRA layout.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create a fully opaque red color
var red = new HBColor(255, 0, 0, 255);
Console.WriteLine(red.Red);   // 255
Console.WriteLine(red.Blue);  // 0
Console.WriteLine(red.Alpha); // 255

// Read palette colors from a font face
var colors = face.GetPaletteColors(0);
foreach (var color in colors)
    Console.WriteLine($"#{color.Alpha:X2}{color.Red:X2}{color.Green:X2}{color.Blue:X2}");
```
